############# 5.3 Lists
list is an ordered collection of values

list = []    notice brackets

It is common (but wrong!) to use a loop variable as a list index

horsemen = ["war", "famine", "pestilence", "death"]
for i in [0, 1, 2, 3}:
    print (horsemen[i])

The above is called list traversal because the variable i is used as an index into the list, printing the i th element but 
it is wrong


better way to go through this is 
horsemen = ["war", "famine", "pestilence", "death"]
for h in horsemen:
