Draw a Cesaro torn line fractal, of the order given by the user. We show four different lines of orders
0,1,2,3. In this example, the angle of the tear is 10 degrees.

Again this is a matter of angles, at least this programmer thinks 



def main(): 

    import turtle

    #set up window
    window = turtle.Screen()
    window.bgcolor("lightgreen")
    alex = turtle.Turtle()

    def koch(tortoise, order, size): 

        """
           Make turtle tortoise draw a cesaro tear of 'order' and 'size'
           Leave the turtle facing the same direction
        """

        if order == 0:				# base case
            tortoise.forward(size)
        else:
            tortoise.forward(size) 
            koch(tortoise, order-1, size/3)	#go 1/3 of the way
            tortoise.right(120)
            koch(tortoise, order-1, size/3)	#go 1/3 of the way
            tortoise.left(10)
            koch(tortoise, order-1, size/3)	#go 1/3 of the way
            tortoise.right(120)
            koch(tortoise,order-1, size/3)

    koch(alex, 1, 10)


